author: @MichaelMueller
text: Hello! Just a note from my site: since Mac OS Catalina z-shell is the default shell ... So if you want to use bash you have to configure it to your default shell ... from the commandline: chsh -s /bin/bash After the change and opening a terminal window you get a warning that the default z-shell is not activated. To suppress this message use: export BASH_SILENCE_DEPRECATION_WARNING=1 in your ~/.bash_profile or ~/.profile For more info see: https://www.howtogeek.com/444596/how-to-change-the-default-shell-to-bash-in-macos-catalina/ and: https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT208050
